      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VERBICI (4) looks a colt of good promise having cruised home on debut in Victoria before taking advantage of the inside draw to lead and win last week's qualifier at this circuit and distance. Starts away from the pegs for the first time but looks to have his share of ability so can continue on his winning way. SUMTHIN DIFFERENT (5) has placed in both starts so far, chasing VERBICI as runner-up here last week. Draws wider but has the scope to improve further. SAN ANTONIO (1) gets the ace draw and the penny may be ready to drop after he showed improvement for second at Menangle last start. REGAL GALA (6) broke in the score-up last week but did a good job to lead and win at Maryborough prior so is capable of better. CORPORATE AFFAIRS (7) showed improvement to place last week and while drawn wider he is open to further progression at start number three.",
